header.gameNote: MEAC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - 1st ROUND AT WINSTON-SALEM NC

article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 64, Coppin St. 58
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- Hillary Haley scored 25 points to lead Maryland-Eastern Shore past Coppin State 64-58 on Wednesday in the first round of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament. Haley was 8 of 12 from the field while Kevin White added 23 points for the sixth-seeded Hawks (11-20). They shot 52.5 percent and held a 34-23 rebounding advantage in advancing to a quarterfinal matchup against No. 3 seed South Carolina State on Thursday. Kareem Brown had 16 points, Ceslovas Kucinskas added 11 and Vince Goldsberry scored 10 for 11th-seeded Coppin State. The Eagles (8-22) shot 39 percent and lost to the Hawks for the third time this season. Neither team could find its 3-point touch. Maryland-Eastern Shore was 3-for-12 from beyond the arc while Coppin State was 4-for-17.
